# 🧠 Kaggle: Measuring Progress Toward AGI — Cognitive Abilities

## 📌 Competition Overview

Google DeepMind has launched a **hackathon-style Kaggle competition** (not a traditional predictive modeling challenge). Instead of training models, participants are tasked with **designing evaluation benchmarks** to measure AI cognitive abilities.

**Goal:** Build tests that evaluate how well frontier AI systems perform on **under-measured cognitive capabilities**.

- 🔗 **Competition Page:** https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/kaggle-measuring-agi  
- 🏢 **Organizer:** Google DeepMind  
- 🧪 **Platform:** Kaggle Community Benchmarks  

---

## 🧩 The Framework: 10 Cognitive Abilities

DeepMind identifies **10 core cognitive abilities** relevant to AGI:

| #  | Ability                | Status                                  |
|----|------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| 1  | Perception             | Well-evaluated                          |
| 2  | Generation             | Well-evaluated                          |
| 3  | Memory                 | Well-evaluated                          |
| 4  | Reasoning              | Well-evaluated                          |
| 5  | Problem Solving        | Well-evaluated                          |
| 6  | **Learning**           | ⚠️ Evaluation Gap — Competition Track   |
| 7  | **Metacognition**      | ⚠️ Evaluation Gap — Competition Track   |
| 8  | **Attention**          | ⚠️ Evaluation Gap — Competition Track   |
| 9  | **Executive Functions**| ⚠️ Evaluation Gap — Competition Track   |
| 10 | **Social Cognition**   | ⚠️ Evaluation Gap — Competition Track   |

👉 You must design benchmarks for one or more of the **5 underserved tracks**.

